# The Dockerfile COPYs nothing — it only `npm install -g`s firebase-tools — so the
# build context needs no files. Excluding everything keeps runtime artifacts
# (firebase-debug.log, data/ exports, firebase.json) out of the tar sent to Docker;
# a live-locked debug log would otherwise break the image build. Docker always
# includes the Dockerfile itself, ignore rule notwithstanding.
*
